All Classes

Class Description
Actor
The Actor class is an abstract class that represents all objects that should have have an image display on screen.
ActorDimensions
ActorDimensions is a class that holds the constants of the sprite dimensions of various Actors.
Car
Car is a PanningActor that moves horizontally on land.
CollisionChecker
CollisionChecker is a utility class that checks for Actor collisions involving a Frog at every tick.
CollisionHandler
CollisionHandler is a utility class that handles the consequences of collisions between Actors.
DeathMessages
DeathMessages is a class which holds the constant Strings of the appropriate death messages to be displayed.
DeathType
DeathType is an enum that tracks the type of death of the player/Frog.
Direction
Direction is an enumeration of all four cardinal directions, used to communicate the Frog's movement direction.
End
End is the goal object that the Frog character must reach.
FilePath
FilePath is a class that stores Strings representing the file paths of resources.
Frog
Frog is a MovableActor that is controlled as the player character.
Game
Game is the model that handles the data and logic during the game.
GameController
GameController is the Controller that handles logic of elements in the Game screen.
HiscoreReader
HiscoreReader reads the top 10 entries from a given hiscore file.
HiscoreWriter
HiscoreWriter writes entries into a hiscore file.
HomeController
HomeController is the Controller that handles logic of elements in the Home screen.
Info
Info is an extension of Game that also relates the progression of the player to the Controller.
InfoController
InfoController is an extension of GameController that handles logic of elements in the Info screen.
Keystroke
Keystroke is a class that defines a HashMap that matches the WASD KeyCode to their cardinal direction.
LaneBuilder
LaneBuilder is a singleton utility class that uses the Prototype, Builder and Factory pattern to instantiate lanes of PanningActors.
Level
Level class is submodel of Game that handles the presence of different Actors in each level.
LevelConfigs
LevelConfigs is a class that constructs, stores and returns the lanes of PanningActors for each level.
Log
Log is a PanningActor that moves horizontally in water.
Main
The Main class of the application.
MovableActor
The MovableActor class is an abstract class that represents displayed objects that must move and receive tick events.
MusicPlayer
MusicPlayer is a singleton utility enum that handles background music.
PanningActor
PanningActor is an abstract class that extends as moving objects during gameplay that also check for collision.
ScorePopupController
ScorePopupController is the Controller that handles logic of elements in the ScorePopup screen
StageDimensions
StageDimensions is a class that stores common constants about the stage's dimensions.
StageManager
StageManager is a singleton utility class which handles the stages of the app.
Turtle
Turtle is a PanningActor that moves horizontally in water.
TutorialFrog
TutorialFrog is an extension of Frog that also tracks the progression of the player up the screen.
TutorialLevel
TutorialLevel is an extension of Level that handles specific PanningActors in the tutorial.
WetTurtle
WetTurtle is a PanningActor that moves horizontally in water, and is also "sunk" every fourth frame.
